HEADWORD: Hamal
<hw>Ha*mal"</hw> <pr>(h⟦adot⟧*m⟦aum⟧l")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>hammal</asp>, <asp>hummaul</asp>,
<asp>hamaul</asp>, <asp>khamal</asp>, etc.]</altsp> <ety>[Turk. & Ar.
<ets>hamm⟦amac⟧l</ets>, fr. Ar. <ets>hamala</ets> to carry.]</ety>
<def>In Turkey and other Oriental countries, a porter or burden bearer;
specif., in Western India, a palanquin bearer.</def>⟦br⟧
